<?php
/**
 * Release focus. Possible values:
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_INITIAL - Initial announcement
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MINORFEATURE - Minor feature enhancement
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MAJORFEATURE - Major feature enhancement
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MINORBUG - Minor bugfixes
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MAJORBUG - Major bugfixes
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MINORSECURITY - Minor security fixes
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MAJORSECURITY - Major security fixes
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_DOCS - Documentation improvements
 */
$this->notes['fm']['focus'] = array(Horde_Release::FOCUS_MINORBUG, Horde_Release::FOCUS_MINORFEATURE);

/* Mailing list release notes. */
$this->notes['ml']['changes'] = <<<ML
The Horde Team is pleased to announce the final release of the Horde Groupware
Webmail Edition version 4.0.3.

Horde Groupware Webmail Edition is a free, enterprise ready, browser based
communication suite. Users can read, send and organize email messages with
four different webmail interfaces and manage and share calendars, contacts,
tasks and notes with the standards compliant components from the Horde
Project.

For upgrading instructions, please see
http://www.horde.org/apps/webmail/docs/UPGRADING

For detailed installation and configuration instructions, please see
http://www.horde.org/apps/webmail/docs/INSTALL

The major changes compared to the Horde Groupware Webmail Edition version 4.0.2
are:

General changes:
    * Added account locking and tracking of failed logins.
    * Fixed title of tasks portal block.
    * Fixed write support for LDAP groups.
    * Small bugfixes and improvements.

Mail changes:
    * Improved display and switching of reply method in dynamic view.
    * Added display and switching of reply method to standard view.
    * Improved search features.
    * Improved button design in dynamic view.
    * Added filter for automatically generated messages.
    * Added flag to indicate mailing list messages.
    * Added ability to hide deleted messages to dynamic view.
    * Fixed manual filtering in INBOX.

Address book changes:
    * Added more default attributes.

Filters changes:
    * Fixed disabling of actions.
    * Fixed sorting of blacklists and whitelists.

Calendar changes:
    * Always synchronize the default calendar.
    * Support snoozing alarms with Sundbird/Lightning.
    * Support VALARM components from iCalendar 2.0 data.
    * Fixed displaying of freebusy data in dynamic view.
ML;

/* Freshmeat release notes, not more than 600 characters. */
$this->notes['fm']['changes'] = <<<FM
Added account locking and tracking of failed logins.
Fixed title of tasks portal block.
Fixed write support for LDAP groups.
Improved email searching, display and switching of reply methods and button design.
Added mail filter for automatic messages and flag for mailing list messages.
Added ability to hide deleted messages to dynamic view.
Added more default address book attributes.
Fixed disabling of filter actions.
Always synchronize the default calendar.
Support snoozing alarms with Sundbird/Lightning.
Support VALARM components from iCalendar 2.0 data.
Fixed displaying of freebusy data.
FM;

$this->notes['name'] = 'Horde Groupware Webmail Edition';
$this->notes['list'] = 'horde';
$this->notes['fm']['project'] = 'horde-webmail';
